    <string name="btn_help">Help</string>
    <string name="btn_close">Close</string>
    <string name="help_content"><![CDATA[
<b>Welcome to Sound Assistant!</b><br/><br/>

This app helps you configure different notification sounds for your apps.<br/><br/>

<b>1. New Apps</b><br/>
Shows apps that have sent notifications with sound but have not yet been configured. Tap an entry to open the app\'s notification settings and configure a sound.<br/><br/>

<b>2. Seen Apps</b><br/>
Shows apps that you have already opened the settings for. Here you can:<br/>
• Mark as New: Move back to \"New Apps\" list<br/>
• Remove: Delete from the list<br/><br/>

<b>3. Last 5 Notifications</b><br/>
Shows the most recent notifications with sounds. Tap an entry to open the notification settings of that app.<br/><br/>

<b>4. Test Notification</b><br/>
Sends a test notification to verify that the app is working correctly.<br/><br/>

<b>Important Notes:</b><br/>
• The app only monitors notifications with sound<br/>
• System notifications are automatically filtered<br/>
• The content of your notifications is never read or stored<br/>
• Only the app name and time are captured<br/><br/>

<b>Tip:</b> Different apps can have multiple notification categories. Make sure you configure the sound for the correct category in the app settings.
    ]]></string>

